<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1143,151,813]" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">
Discussion: The recognition of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Betrem" authorityYear="1972" box="[490,738,513,537]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Micromeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureola">
<emphasis box="[490,738,513,537]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">Micromeriella aureola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[798,918,513,537]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Micromeriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalina">
<emphasis box="[798,918,513,537]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">M. hyalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based mainly on colour characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Osten, T." box="[351,491,544,568]" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitrage" pageId="1" pageNumber="7" pagination="537 - 593" part="32" refId="ref2597" refString="Osten, T. (2000). Die Scoliiden des Mittelmeer-Gebietes und angrenzender Regionen (Hymenoptera). Ein Bestimmungsschlussel. Linzer biologische Beitrage, 32: 537 - 593." title="Die Scoliiden des Mittelmeer-Gebietes und angrenzender Regionen (Hymenoptera). Ein Bestimmungsschlussel" type="journal article" year="2000">Osten, 2000</bibRefCitation>
) and is difficult, especially in males. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gadallah, N. S." box="[952,1138,543,568]" journalOrPublisher="Efflatounia" pageId="1" pageNumber="7" pagination="31 - 40" part="4" refId="ref2565" refString="Gadallah, N. S. (2004): Scoliidae from the Western Region of Saudi Arabia (Hymenoptera: Aculeata). Efflatounia, 4: 31 - 40." title="Scoliidae from the Western Region of Saudi Arabia (Hymenoptera: Aculeata)" type="journal article" year="2004">Gadallah (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, mentions a new character, the spatulate and apically enlarged outer spur on the hind tibia of 
<emphasis box="[136,257,605,629]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">M. aureola</emphasis>
, what is narrow and pointed in 
<emphasis box="[614,732,605,629]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">M. hyalina</emphasis>
. This character is marked in females and weaker, but also visible in males.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1143,151,813]" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">
Note: Sometimes the specific name 
<emphasis box="[547,648,666,690]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">hyalinata</emphasis>
is used in combination with 
<taxonomicName authority="Betrem, 1972" authorityName="Betrem" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Micromeriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[988,1142,666,690]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">Micromeriella</emphasis>
Betrem, 1972
</taxonomicName>
. That is incorrect. The species 
<emphasis box="[645,746,697,721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">hyalinata</emphasis>
Sichel, 1864, was described in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[208,455,727,751]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[208,275,727,751]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">Scolia</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1775
</taxonomicName>
, and is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[703,770,727,751]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[703,770,727,751]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">Scolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Betrem" authorityYear="1927" box="[788,923,727,751]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Austroscolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[788,923,727,751]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">Austroscolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<emphasis box="[940,1028,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="7">carnifex</emphasis>
Coquerel, 1855.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
